Taiwo Awoniyi and his teammates at Nottingham Forest welcomed a new assistant coach following the departure of Steven Reid. Awoniyi who joined the team on a club-record transfer from Union Berlin in the Bundesliga is expected to lead the attack of the team when the English Premier League (EPL) begins next month and will now work with Jamie Robinson as first team coach. Having enjoyed a 13-year playing career with clubs including Liverpool and Barnsley, Robinson joins The Reds following 11 years with the Football Association as Head of Professional Game Coach Development at St. George’s Park.   Wilder wants to fight winner of Joshua –Usyk rematch     Ejuke: why I joined Hertha Berlin     NPFL: Remo Stars, Kwara United in titanic race for third…   He is expected to work closely with Forest Head Coach Steve Cooper during his time with the FA and with The Reds. “It’s an incredibly exciting time to join Nottingham Forest and I’m looking forward to the challenge ahead in building on our return to the Premier League,” said Jamie Robinson. “I’ve known Steve Cooper for many years and we’ve worked together closely in previous roles. Steve Cooper said: “Jamie is an outstanding coach who has worked closely with, and supported the development of, many elite level players and coaches during his time with The FA.”